ngland","Betchworth, Surrey, England":"Betchworth, Surrey, England","Holme Lacy, Herefordshire, England":"Holme Lacy, Herefordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Scudamore","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Skidmore  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Skidmore","meanings":["English (Staffordshire): of Norman origin, a variant of <b>Scudamore</b>, which most probably arises from a Norman French nickname for a knight who used a particular type of leather shield, from the unrecorded Norman French phrase, <i>escu de more</i> ‘Moor's shield’, a reference to a type of Moorish leather shield called an <i>adarga</i>, which was in widespread use not only in medieval Iberia and north Africa but also in Brittany.","History: The manor of Upton Scudamore in Wiltshire was held by Peter de Skydemore in 1216. The same manor was held by Godfrey Escudamore shortly after 1150. The Scudamore family claim descent from Ralph, recorded in Domesday Book (1086) as holder of <i>Opeton</i> (Upton), whose son was known as Reginald <i>Escudemor</i>."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ann Scudamore was born in 1383, in Betchworth, Surrey, England, her father, Philip Scudamore, was 35 and her mother, Agnes Huntercombe, was 29. She married Henry le Moyns II in 1400, in Surrey, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1430, in her hometown, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1383–1430":"1383–1430","1389–1442":"1389–1442","1395–1485":"1395–1485","1376–1402":"1376–1402","1402–1444":"1402–1444","1348–1419":"1348–1419","1355–1411":"1355–1411","1395":"1395","1383":"1383","9 December 1419":"9. detsember 1419","14 May 1411":"14. mai 1411","